---
import GuideLayout from "../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";
import { qatarVisas } from "../../data/qatar/visas";
import { buildBreadcrumbs, buildFAQSchema } from "../../lib/seo";
import RelatedLinks from "../../components/ui/RelatedLinks.astro";
import SourcesBlock from "../../components/ui/SourcesBlock.astro";
import FAQAccordion from "../../components/ui/FAQAccordion.astro";
const faqs = [
  { question: "How do I get a work visa for Qatar?", answer: "Your Qatar employer initiates the visa process through the Ministry of Interior. You enter on a temporary entry permit, complete medical testing, and receive your Residence Permit and Qatar ID. The process takes 2-6 weeks." },
  { question: "Can I change employers in Qatar?", answer: "Yes. Qatar reformed its labor laws to allow workers to change employers without the previous employer's consent, provided proper notice is given as per the employment contract." },
  { question: "Does Qatar offer permanent residency?", answer: "Yes. Qatar introduced a permanent residency program for long-term residents (10+ years) and those with significant contributions to the country. Annual allocations are limited." },
  { question: "Is there a minimum salary to sponsor family in Qatar?", answer: "Yes. You need a minimum salary of QAR 10,000 per month to sponsor family members (spouse and children)." },
  { question: "Do I need an exit permit to leave Qatar?", answer: "No. Exit permits have been abolished for most workers in Qatar. Workers can leave the country without employer permission." },
];
const breadcrumbs = [{ name: "Home", url: "https://gulfexpathub.com/" }, { name: "Qatar", url: "https://gulfexpathub.com/qatar/guide/" }, { name: "Visa Guide", url: "https://gulfexpathub.com/qatar/visa-guide/" }];
---
<GuideLayout title="Qatar Visa Guide 2026: Work, Residency, Family" description="Complete Qatar visa guide for 2026. Work visa, permanent residency, and family visa requirements, costs, and processing times explained." canonical="/qatar/visa-guide/" schemas={[buildBreadcrumbs(breadcrumbs), buildFAQSchema(faqs)]} breadcrumbs={[{ name: "Home", url: "/" }, { name: "Qatar", url: "/qatar/guide/" }, { name: "Visa Guide", url: "/qatar/visa-guide/" }]}>
<h1>Qatar Visa Guide 2026</h1>
<p>Qatar's visa system has undergone significant reform, particularly following the labor law changes introduced ahead of and after the 2022 FIFA World Cup. The dismantling of the kafala system, introduction of job mobility, and abolition of exit permits have modernized the framework substantially. This guide covers the main visa categories available to expatriates in Qatar, along with requirements, costs, and practical advice for 2026.</p>
{qatarVisas.types.map((visa) => (<><h2>{visa.name}</h2><p><strong>Duration:</strong> {visa.duration}</p><p>{visa.process}</p><p><strong>Estimated cost:</strong> {visa.cost}</p><h3>Requirements</h3><ul>{visa.requirements.map((r) => <li>{r}</li>)}</ul></>))}
<h2>General Information</h2>
<ul>{qatarVisas.generalNotes.map((n) => <li>{n}</li>)}</ul>
<p>The Qatar visa process is managed through the Ministry of Interior, with many services available through the Metrash2 mobile app and online portal. Employers handle most work visa processes and are legally required to bear the costs. The Qatar ID (QID) is the primary identification document for residents and is required for banking, healthcare, and other services. Processing times have improved significantly with digitization, and most visa applications are processed within the stated timeframes.</p>
<FAQAccordion faqs={faqs} />
<SourcesBlock sources={[{ name: "Qatar MOI", url: "https://portal.moi.gov.qa/" }, { name: "Qatar MADLSA", url: "https://www.adlsa.gov.qa/" }]} />
<RelatedLinks links={[{ label: "Qatar Expat Guide", href: "/qatar/guide/" }, { label: "Qatar Salaries", href: "/qatar/salaries/" }, { label: "Qatar Labor Law", href: "/qatar/labor-law/" }]} />
</GuideLayout>
